Multiple Grammy Award-winning singer Adele performed a special one-night only concert in New York at Radio City Music Hall on Tuesday, Nov. 17. The event was recorded for a one-hour NBC special, "Adele Live in New York City," which aired last night, Monday, Dec. 14 (10 p.m. ET/PT). Watch the special in full below!

The one-hour NBC special showcased Adeleâ€™s incredible performances of songs from her new album, "25." The show also features Adele interacting with her fans from the iconic Radio City stage, and performing landmark songs from throughout her career. Cameras were rolling behind-the-scenes in the days leading up to the concert, offering exclusive access to the artistsâ€™ preparations for this extraordinary event.
